result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey A Reinke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Stipulation to restitution amount.  Joint and several obligation of $351.01 and sole obligation of $354.00.
If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not possess or use pornography and/or sexually explicit materials.

Defendant shall have no contact with M.A.T. or her residence.

Defendant shall pay any supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.

Defendant shall comply with sex offender registration.

Defendant shall comply with sex offender treatment and assessment.

Defendant shall submit to random urine/drug screens.

timeConds.notes: With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.

supervisions.notes: Per Court 12-26-18 grant additional time served for total of 217 days sentence credit.

superMiscConds.notes:
Per Court 9-13-16 remove occupation or volunteer position restriction. 

Defendant shall have access to internet useage by electronic devices only with the speicifcation of the agent and limited by the permission as given to him.

All conditions indicated in the Judgment of Conviction dated February 3, 2015 shall remain in full force and effect.  

Court enters judgment for unpaid financial obligations.
